title: Jamie Redknapp: These two teams will miss out on the top four
text:
1 of 12 Express Sport brings you our Premier League Team of the Week from Gameweek 29 
Arsenal meanwhile look to be on a downwards spiral - winning just one league game in their last five outings. 
With Arsene Wenger ’s future in doubt, Arsenal sit sixth in the table, six points adrift of Liverpool. 
And Redknapp doesn’t think Chelsea, Tottenham, Manchester City or the Reds will find themselves replaced by United or Liverpool in the Champions League places come the end of the season. 
"I think Arsenal will miss out, possibly United as well,” Redknapp told Sky Sports. GETTY Jose Mourinho's side have gone 18 games unbeaten in the league but remain fifth Most valuable players in the world revealed Thu, March 16, 2017
